Brute Force--Treat like normal tree  Forget that it's a BST.
For every node:
Check if p exists in left subtree.
Check if q exists in left subtree.
Check if they are on different sides.

Time = O(N²)
Space = O(H)

Better Brute Force
Find path from root to p.
Find path from root to q.
Then compare both paths.

Time- O(N)


OPTIMAL-
TreeNode* lca(TreeNode* root, int p, int q)
{
    while(root)
    {
        if(p < root->data && q < root->data)
            root = root->left;

        else if(p > root->data && q > root->data)
            root = root->right;

        else
            return root;
    }

    return NULL;
}


